14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
15 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
16 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 6224 of Title 36, unless there
17 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
18 Under any method of compensation, the total commission payable
19 to the public insurance adjuster, including expenses, direct costs,
20 or any other costs accrued by the public insurance adjuster, shall
21 not exceed ten percent (10%) of the amount of the insurance
22 settlement when adjusting for entities subject to The Governmental
23 Tort Claims Act, Section 151 et seq. of Title 51 of the Oklahoma
24 Statutes.
